name: Butler Library Study Room 402
description: Located in Butler Library's fourth floor, this premium study room features floor-to-ceiling windows offering views of campus, built-in whiteboards on three walls, and ergonomic seating. The space includes USB charging ports, adjustable LED lighting, and sound-dampening wall panels for optimal study conditions.

name: Lerner Hall Classroom 555
description: Situated in the heart of Lerner Hall, this modern classroom converts to a flexible study space during non-class hours. Features include movable furniture for group or individual study, a smart board, multiple power outlets, and natural lighting through large windows overlooking Broadway. Perfect for group projects and collaborative work.

name: Avery Library Reading Room
description: A quiet sanctuary within the Avery library, this reading room combines classic architecture with modern amenities. High ceilings and traditional wood furnishings create a focused study environment. Individual desk lamps, comfortable chairs, and built-in power stations at each table make this an ideal spot for long study sessions.

name: Milstein Center Study Room 302
description: Set within the historic Avery Architectural & Fine Arts Library, this study area offers a unique blend of inspiration and functionality. The space features custom-designed reading tables, specialized task lighting, and proximity to the architectural collection. Large windows provide abundant natural light and views of the adjacent courtyard.

name: Mathematics Library Study Area
description: Modern study room with a large table and TV screen for presentations.

name: Kent Hall Study Lounge
description: Comfortable study lounge with couches and study tables.

name: Northwest Corner Building Room 501
description: Located on the 5th floor of the Northwest Corner Building, this modern study lounge offers panoramic views of the Hudson River. The space features contemporary furniture, height-adjustable tables, and state-of-the-art climate control. Multiple power outlets and high-speed Wi-Fi make it perfect for tech-heavy study sessions.

name: Hamilton Hall Room 302
description: Classic classroom setting with chalkboards and movable desks.

name: Butler Library Room 209
description: Intimate study room with vintage wooden furniture and natural lighting.

name: Pupin Physics Laboratory Room 428
description: Located in the historic Pupin Physics Laboratory, this versatile classroom features state-of-the-art demonstration equipment, multiple chalkboards, and tiered seating optimized for physics lectures and group work. The room offers excellent sightlines, integrated AV equipment, and ample natural lighting through its large windows overlooking the campus. Perfect for STEM study groups and technical discussions.

name: Uris Library Business Commons
description: State-of-the-art business commons featuring Bloomberg terminals, dual-monitor workstations, and collaborative pods with integrated displays. The space includes a coffee bar, printing station, and private phone booths for calls. Popular among Business School students for market research and group projects.

name: Mudd Engineering Library Room 251
description: Specialized engineering study room equipped with CAD workstations, 3D visualization software, and a materials sample library. Features include adjustable standing desks, specialized task lighting, and a collaborative workspace with digital drawing tablets.

name: International Affairs Building Room 501
description: Global-focused classroom featuring video conferencing equipment for international connections, simultaneous interpretation booths, and interactive world maps. Perfect for international relations seminars and cross-cultural project collaborations.

name: East Asian Library Reading Room
description: This serene reading room in the C.V. Starr East Asian Library provides a contemplative study environment. Traditional Asian design elements combine with modern study amenities, including custom-built wooden tables, individual reading lamps, and ergonomic seating. The space offers a peaceful atmosphere away from campus bustle.

name: Law Library Study Suite 303
description: Premium study suite in the Law Library featuring sound-insulated walls and doors for maximum privacy. Includes a large conference table, comfortable executive chairs, and a dedicated whiteboard wall. Built-in shelving and a window view of Amsterdam Avenue make this space ideal for focused legal study sessions.

name: Jerome L. Greene Science Center Room 405
description: Located in the cutting-edge Greene Science Center, this study space combines neuroscience-informed design with practical functionality. Features include circadian lighting systems that adjust throughout the day, sound-masking technology for optimal concentration, and ergonomic furniture designed for long study sessions. The room offers panoramic views of Manhattanville campus and includes a dedicated break area with hydration station.

name: School of Social Work Library Commons
description: A welcoming collaborative space in the School of Social Work featuring zones for both individual and group work. The commons includes private pods with acoustic panels for sensitive conversations, adjustable-height workstations, and a meditation corner with comfortable seating. Large windows provide views of Morningside Heights, while smart glass technology prevents glare and maintains optimal temperature.

name: Journalism School Multimedia Lab
description: State-of-the-art multimedia lab equipped with professional-grade audio-visual equipment and editing stations. Each workstation features dual 4K monitors, professional editing software, and broadcast-quality audio interfaces. The space includes a small recording booth for audio projects, collaborative worktables, and a media presentation wall for group critiques.

name: Teachers College Collaborative Commons
description: Innovative learning space designed to support education research and collaboration. Features include interactive smart boards, flexible furniture arrangements for various group sizes, and a dedicated maker space corner with supplies for educational materials. The room incorporates natural materials and plants to create a biophilic environment that enhances focus and creativity.

name: Columbia Business School Trading Lab
description: Professional-grade trading room featuring real-time financial data feeds and market analysis tools. Equipped with Bloomberg terminals, Reuters data access, and specialized financial software. The space includes dual-monitor workstations, a stock ticker display, and breakout areas for team strategy sessions. Perfect for finance research and market analysis projects.
